21 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 64 O.S. 2021, Section 1002, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 1002. In order that the state school lands may be
24 administered in a manner to assure their preservation as well as the
Req. No. 17031 Page 2

1 appr eciation of the trust estate and the maximum return from the use
2 of state school lands for the support and maintenance of the common
3 schools of the state, the Commissioners of the Land Office, as
4 trustees of the state school lands, are hereby authorized and
5 empowered to:
6 1. Categorize the state school lands as agricultural or,
7 commercial, or investment according to the use which the
8 Commissioners of the Land Office determine from time to time to be
9 most beneficial to the interest of the present and future
10 beneficiaries of the this state;
11 2. Sell, at public auction after appraisement, the surface
12 interest in any state school land categorized by the Commissioners
13 of the Land Office to be excess or when determined to be in the best
14 interest of the trust;
15 3. Institute projects to develop and improve those state school
16 lands which are categorized as commercial or investment lands;
17 4. Acquire by exchange, purchase, gift, or grant all real
18 property and to acquire by exchange, purchase, gift, or grant all
19 personal property including donations and funds necessary for the
20 purpose of utilizing trust lands for the development of commercial
21 and, agricultural, investment, oil and gas, or other leases or
22 Commissioners of the Land Office operations to maximize trust income
23 for present and future beneficiaries; and
24
Req. No. 17031 Page 3

1 5. Exchange any real property of the trust for other real
2 property of equal or greater value to maximize income for present
3 and future beneficiaries, in accordance with and under the safeguard
4 of trust requirements; and
5 6. Purchase, own, and operate motor vehicles necessary for use
6 in their operations and purchase insurance on such motor vehicles in
7 accordance with statutory provisions and subject to the approval of
